The Machakos government is to blame for illegal sand harvesting in Mavoloni, Kisiiki and Ndalani towns, Yatta MP Francis Mwangangi has said.He said the county continues to license and collect taxes from the owners of lorries, despite a ban early this year.Mwangangi spoke at St James Secondary School in Ilumanthi village on Monday. We had a meeting that brought together the political leadership in this region and the government led by the deputy county commissioner. We agreed there would be no more sand harvesting. But the county has failed to walk the talk, he said.Mwangangi said that the county is yet to pull down its tax collecting barriers.